# Data Layer — Services, Queries & Hooks

## Architecture Overview

```
UI Component
  └─ Custom Hook (useQuery / useMutation)
       └─ queryKeys.ts (typed cache keys)
       └─ Service (extends BaseService)
            └─ Supabase client  /  Storyblok client  /  Vimeo API
```

Never call services or Supabase directly from a component. Always go through TanStack Query.

## BaseService Cheat Sheet

Import from `@/services/api/baseService`:

```typescript
import { BaseService, AppError, AppErrorCode } from '@/services/api/baseService';
import type { PaginatedResponse, FilterParam, QueryOptions } from '@/services/api/baseService';
```

### Creating a new service

```typescript
export class ExampleService extends BaseService {
  protected tableName = 'example_table';

  // Simple list with filters
  async getByUser(userId: string): Promise<Example[]> {
    return this.list<Example>({
      filters: [{ field: 'user_id', operator: 'eq', value: userId }],
      sort: [{ field: 'created_at', ascending: false }],
    });
  }

  // Single record
  async getById(id: string): Promise<Example> {
    return this.get<Example>(id);
  }

  // Insert with auto user_id injection
  async create(data: Omit<Example, 'id' | 'user_id' | 'created_at'>): Promise<Example> {
    return this.createWithUser<Example, typeof data>(data);
  }

  // Upsert on conflict
  async upsert(data: ExampleInput): Promise<Example> {
    return this.upsertWithConflict<Example, ExampleInput>(data, {
      onConflict: 'user_id,some_id',
    });
  }

  // RPC call
  async callMyRpc(userId: string): Promise<RpcResult> {
    return this.executeRpc<RpcResult>('my_rpc_name', { p_user_id: userId });
  }

  // Paginated
  async listPaged(page: number): Promise<PaginatedResponse<Example>> {
    return this.listPaginated<Example>({
      pagination: { page, limit: 20 },
      sort: [{ field: 'created_at', ascending: false }],
    });
  }
}

export const exampleService = new ExampleService();
```

### Filter operators

`eq`, `neq`, `gt`, `gte`, `lt`, `lte`, `like`, `ilike`, `in`, `is`

